cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper is about object detection and semantic segmentation using convolutional neural networks (CNNs), which are commonly used in computer vision research. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of supervised pre-training and fine-tuning, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning research, suggesting that it could also be categorized as cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a new algorithm for object detection, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper compares its approach to a recently proposed sliding-window detector, which could also place it in the cs.MM (Multimedia) category.
